snippet.textDisplay:
BRAAAAADDDDDDDD!!!!

Explain something to me. What is the difference between high lift & bleach.

I used to do platinum bleach from boxes and I had what my hairdresser called a chemical cut from over processing my hair and it would just break off.

So I stopped using boxed dyes and got my hair back to my mucky dirty dishwater blonde hair.

Now I only use a ash blonde high lift with 20 vol developer and will use wella toner with 20 in between highlights to keep the yellows and orange away, it keeps it pretty ash blonde and now my hair is so healthy, in fact I just had to get 6 inches cut off because it was too long!

Why is doing a high lift so much more healthy for my hair compared to doing a bleach??

My mom now does the same to her hair and her hair is so amazingly healthy now too!

snippet.textDisplay: Just went blonde again . I have done it several times and have never had an issue with it. I bleach, wash with just shampoo, tone, wash with purple shampoo leave for a couple of minutes rinse than purple conditioner leave in for a little rinse than do a deep conditioning and or mask. Than leave it in for a few minutes or leave it over night. Than dont touch my hair for a couple of days and tone it again if I need to. If that dont work than i can or will get a hair dye I like . And I dooo not do box dye !!

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Brad, can you do a video with tips for people with fine/thin hair or bald spots? Recently I'm having a massive hair loss because of stress and I do not know how to manage my hair anymore... I always had fine/thin hair, but never bald spots. I'm even afraid to brush it or style it. I'm losing all my confidence and self-esteem together with my hair. I think a video about this subject can help not only me but a lot of people with similar experiences.

Tomorrow I'm going to a hair salon for a short haircut. Hopping for it to look a little better.
I also have gone to a doctor for treatment. But he said it could take some time until a noticeable change in the hair.

I love your videos, you are amazing.

sorry for my poor English, it's not my mother language. ☹

🥰
